Insider Activity


Individual




Ziad S. Ojakli



Mr. Ziad S. Ojakli is Group VP-Government & Community Relations at Ford Motor Co. He is on the Board of Directors at The National Civil Rights Museum, The Washington Center for Internships & Academic Seminars, Alliance of Automobile Manufacturers, Inc., Arab American Community Center for Economic & Social Services, Canadian American Business Council, Jackie Robinson Foundation, Michigan Manufacturers Association, National Association of Manufacturers, and Centro Fox.
Mr. Ojakli was previously employed as a Principal by The White House.
He received his undergraduate degree from Georgetown University.



